<section id="command-hideturtle">
<title>HIDETURTLE</title>
<indexterm><primary>HIDETURTLE</primary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>HT</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>HIDETURTLE</command>
<command>HT</command></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Makes the turtle invisible.
To make the turtle visible again, call <link linkend="command-showturtle">SHOWTURTLE</link>.
</para>

<para>
It's a good idea to hide the turtle just before you start a complicated drawing, because hiding the turtle speeds up the drawing substantially.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<programlisting><userinput>HIDETURTLE
SHOWTURTLE</userinput>
</programlisting>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>
</section>
